1
00:00:07,018 --> 00:00:11,455
<i>We are Fighting Dreamers aiming high</i>

2
00:00:11,522 --> 00:00:15,049
<i>Fighting Dreamers</i>
<i>don't care what people think about them</i>

3
00:00:15,126 --> 00:00:18,562
<i>Fighting Dreamers</i>
<i>follow what they believe</i>

4
00:00:18,629 --> 00:00:22,224
<i>Oli Oli Oli Oh! Just go my way</i>

5
00:00:22,299 --> 00:00:25,564
<i>Right here right now (Bang)</i>
<i>Hit it straight like a line drive!</i>

6
00:00:25,636 --> 00:00:27,570
<i>Right here right now (Burn)</i>

7
00:00:29,373 --> 00:00:32,308
<i>Down a difficult road</i>
<i>filled with endless struggles</i>

8
00:00:32,376 --> 00:00:36,176
<i>Where do you think you are going</i>
<i>following someone else's map?</i>

9
00:00:36,580 --> 00:00:43,418
<i>An insightful crow comes along</i>
<i>to tear up the map</i>

10
00:00:43,654 --> 00:00:50,719
<i>Now open your eyes and</i>
<i>take a look at the truth (Yeah!)</i>

11
00:00:51,028 --> 00:00:57,160
<i>There's nothing to lose,</i>
<i>so let's GO!!!</i>

12
00:00:57,301 --> 00:01:01,567
<i>We are Fighting Dreamers aiming high</i>

13
00:01:01,639 --> 00:01:05,234
<i>Fighting Dreamers</i>
<i>don't care what people think about them</i>

14
00:01:05,309 --> 00:01:08,642
<i>Fighting Dreamers</i>
<i>follow what they believe</i>

15
00:01:08,712 --> 00:01:12,341
<i>Oli Oli Oli Oh!</i>
<i>Just go my way</i>

16
00:01:12,416 --> 00:01:16,011
<i>Right here right now (Bang)</i>
<i>Hit it straight like a line drive!</i>

17
00:01:16,087 --> 00:01:19,579
<i>Right here right now (Burn)</i>
<i>We're gonna do it and do our best!</i>

18
00:01:19,657 --> 00:01:23,115
<i>Right here right now (Bang)</i>
<i>Hit it straight like a line drive!</i>

19
00:01:23,327 --> 00:01:27,423
<i>Right here right now (Burn)</i>
<i>We're gonna do it and do our best! BANG!</i>

20
00:01:40,421 --> 00:01:42,412
We're almost at
the Village Hidden in the Leaves.

21
00:01:43,191 --> 00:01:44,055
Is everybody here?

22
00:01:44,392 --> 00:01:45,120
- Yes, sir!
- Yes, sir!

23
00:01:48,129 --> 00:01:50,757
Big Brother Omasa,
we're missing one!

24
00:01:51,466 --> 00:01:53,024
What? Who is it?!

25
00:01:55,069 --> 00:01:57,003
It's Idate! Morino Idate!

26
00:01:58,806 --> 00:02:00,603
Darn, he's such a hopeless kid!

27
00:02:01,209 --> 00:02:02,836
What should we do?
Shall we wait?

28
00:02:03,578 --> 00:02:04,567
We have no choice...

29
00:02:06,114 --> 00:02:06,671
What the?!

30
00:02:07,348 --> 00:02:08,110
Who is it?!

31
00:02:10,018 --> 00:02:13,078
You people are from the Wasabi Family
of the Land of Tea, correct?

32
00:02:13,755 --> 00:02:15,052
Who are you!

33
00:02:19,427 --> 00:02:21,520
You should know your place.

34
00:02:21,796 --> 00:02:25,061
Hooligans like you people
are no match for a Shinobi!

35
00:02:41,816 --> 00:02:44,910
Please don't worry.
I won't take your lives.

36
00:02:45,420 --> 00:02:46,546
If you've learned from this,

37
00:02:46,621 --> 00:02:49,818
you should give up the race
at Todoroki Great Shrine.

38
00:02:55,163 --> 00:02:55,993
Blast it!

39
00:02:58,199 --> 00:03:01,293
I have to at least deliver this letter
to the Hidden Leaf Village.

40
00:03:23,524 --> 00:03:27,358
OK! Mission! Mission!
I'm so eager to do it!

41
00:03:28,763 --> 00:03:30,822
But Kakashi Sensei is not here.

42
00:03:31,999 --> 00:03:34,058
Is he late as usual?

43
00:03:34,469 --> 00:03:36,334
No, Kakashi will not be coming

44
00:03:37,638 --> 00:03:39,629
It's Old Lady Tsunade!

45
00:03:39,974 --> 00:03:40,963
Don't call me an old lady!

46
00:03:43,478 --> 00:03:45,378
Excuse me... Lady Hokage...

47
00:03:45,880 --> 00:03:48,678
What do you mean by
Kakashi Sensei will not be coming?

48
00:03:49,383 --> 00:03:51,044
As you three already know,

49
00:03:51,686 --> 00:03:55,144
most of the Jonin including Kakashi
are on different missions.

50
00:03:56,190 --> 00:03:59,887
This time, the three of you will have
to execute the mission by yourselves.

51
00:04:01,195 --> 00:04:04,221
This is a B rank mission,
escorting an important figure!

52
00:04:05,199 --> 00:04:07,030
Escorting an important figure...

53
00:04:07,902 --> 00:04:09,426
Of course,
depending on the situation,

54
00:04:09,504 --> 00:04:11,563
the mission has the possibility
of becoming an A-rank.

55
00:04:14,275 --> 00:04:16,243
And, who are we protecting?

56
00:04:17,345 --> 00:04:18,073
Don't know...

57
00:04:18,179 --> 00:04:20,647
What do you mean
"don't know"?!

58
00:04:21,048 --> 00:04:22,538
In the neighboring nation
of the Land of Tea,

59
00:04:22,617 --> 00:04:24,812
they have a Dedication Ceremony
at the Todoroki Great Shrine

60
00:04:24,886 --> 00:04:26,376
once every four years.

61
00:04:27,021 --> 00:04:28,488
We've received a request
to escort the runner

62
00:04:28,556 --> 00:04:31,650
who will be participating in
the race that will be held there.

63
00:04:32,593 --> 00:04:34,788
But an assailant from the opponent's side

64
00:04:34,862 --> 00:04:37,990
attacked the messengers
before they arrived here.

65
00:04:39,801 --> 00:04:40,733
Assailant?

66
00:04:41,102 --> 00:04:44,230
Excuse me, but I still don't
quite understand the mission.

67
00:04:44,872 --> 00:04:49,673
Well, you should get the details
directly from Boss Jirocho.

68
00:04:49,911 --> 00:04:54,507
Boss Jirocho?! Oh yeah!
The boss from that time!

69
00:04:55,249 --> 00:04:56,238
That's it.

70
00:04:56,784 --> 00:04:58,547
Now that you three understand,
depart immediately!

71
00:04:58,886 --> 00:05:01,616
Get to the Land of Tea by today.
Snap to it!

72
00:05:01,956 --> 00:05:02,581
- Yes!
- All right.

73
00:05:02,657 --> 00:05:03,214
Okay!

74
00:05:03,558 --> 00:05:05,025
Roger that!

75
00:05:07,728 --> 00:05:08,592
<i>I'm counting on you.</i>

76
00:05:10,464 --> 00:05:16,425
<i>Mission! Help an Old Friend</i>
<i>in the Land of Tea</i>

77
00:05:23,444 --> 00:05:26,140
Hey Sakura, aren't you hungry?

78
00:05:26,581 --> 00:05:27,741
Well, a little bit...

79
00:05:27,915 --> 00:05:29,382
Then it's decided!

80
00:05:29,584 --> 00:05:33,680
And perfect timing!
There's a teahouse right over there!

81
00:05:34,088 --> 00:05:35,385
Hey, Naruto.

82
00:05:44,498 --> 00:05:45,157
You're here...?

83
00:05:46,033 --> 00:05:48,934
Aoi Rokusho has now arrived.

84
00:05:49,737 --> 00:05:52,331
I had you go through
all that trouble,

85
00:05:52,540 --> 00:05:55,441
but Jirocho of the Wasabi
does not know when to give up.

86
00:05:55,843 --> 00:05:59,040
Is he still trying to take part
in the race at Todoroki Great Shrine?

87
00:05:59,914 --> 00:06:00,778
That's right.

88
00:06:01,515 --> 00:06:05,645
And there's new information
that they have also hired Shinobi.

89
00:06:06,387 --> 00:06:07,149
I see...

90
00:06:08,189 --> 00:06:12,558
Then next time, let's beat them
to a pulp at the race...

91
00:06:17,765 --> 00:06:18,629
Welcome!

92
00:06:18,799 --> 00:06:20,164
Ma'am, I'll have sweet bean soup.

93
00:06:20,501 --> 00:06:21,798
Then I'll have dumplings.

94
00:06:22,503 --> 00:06:23,299
How about you, Sasuke?

95
00:06:24,171 --> 00:06:24,933
Jelly...

96
00:06:25,473 --> 00:06:27,407
All right, please wait for a moment.

97
00:06:34,615 --> 00:06:35,843
<i>Ninja from the Leaf...</i>

98
00:06:36,550 --> 00:06:38,279
I'm gonna work so hard!

99
00:06:38,819 --> 00:06:41,583
Naruto, don't take unnecessary action
by yourself.

100
00:06:41,656 --> 00:06:42,918
Oh, okay.

101
00:06:43,691 --> 00:06:46,285
Having sweet bean soup
when it's so nice outside.

102
00:06:46,794 --> 00:06:49,092
The Ninja profession sure
is carefree!

103
00:06:49,730 --> 00:06:50,958
What did you say?

104
00:06:52,566 --> 00:06:55,126
Things must really be peaceful
for the Leaf Village.

105
00:06:55,603 --> 00:06:57,696
Such a dense looking
bunch of guys...

106
00:06:59,073 --> 00:06:59,801
What?!

107
00:07:00,241 --> 00:07:03,438
Hey! I didn't know there was
such a cutie here.

108
00:07:04,278 --> 00:07:05,643
I take back that previous comment!

109
00:07:06,414 --> 00:07:07,608
Ah... pardon me.

110
00:07:07,848 --> 00:07:09,406
I'm Idate Morino.

111
00:07:10,117 --> 00:07:12,085
What's your name, young lady?

112
00:07:12,153 --> 00:07:14,951
Don't you talk to Sakura
in such a familiar tone!

113
00:07:15,156 --> 00:07:17,954
Sakura... That's a good name.

114
00:07:18,626 --> 00:07:21,561
Hey, even a chance meeting is due
to karma from a previous life.

115
00:07:21,729 --> 00:07:23,560
Why don't we talk about our future?

116
00:07:24,632 --> 00:07:28,159
Huh? Talk about... the future?

117
00:07:28,703 --> 00:07:33,402
I'm talking about you quitting
the Ninja life and becoming my bride...

118
00:07:33,641 --> 00:07:36,804
Hey you! How dare you
hit on her all of a sudden!

119
00:07:36,978 --> 00:07:38,070
Don't be silly!

120
00:07:38,679 --> 00:07:40,510
Just joking.

121
00:07:41,248 --> 00:07:42,510
But hey, you fool!

122
00:07:42,917 --> 00:07:46,011
Idate here hates Ninja!

123
00:07:46,754 --> 00:07:48,654
If you wander around
the Land of Tea anymore,

124
00:07:48,723 --> 00:07:49,917
there'll be a price to pay!

125
00:07:50,157 --> 00:07:52,785
That's amusing! Bring it on!

126
00:07:57,398 --> 00:07:58,592
Hey, Naruto!

127
00:07:59,367 --> 00:08:02,803
Ridiculous! We don't have time
to waste on a hooligan.

128
00:08:03,270 --> 00:08:04,567
Be quiet, Sasuke!

129
00:08:04,839 --> 00:08:07,399
I'm not going to forgive a guy
who makes fun of Shinobi!

130
00:08:07,742 --> 00:08:09,835
I'm going to punish this guy...

131
00:08:09,910 --> 00:08:10,535
Huh?

132
00:08:11,479 --> 00:08:12,411
He's gone...

133
00:08:13,314 --> 00:08:15,714
<i>Impossible!</i>
<i>I didn't even notice...</i>

134
00:08:18,052 --> 00:08:19,849
Where did that guy run away to?!

135
00:08:20,154 --> 00:08:21,678
Here, thank you for waiting.

136
00:08:23,124 --> 00:08:24,648
Dang it!

137
00:08:25,426 --> 00:08:27,053
Thank you for your patronage.

138
00:08:28,095 --> 00:08:29,858
What? Two bills?

139
00:08:31,032 --> 00:08:31,828
This is...?

140
00:08:32,366 --> 00:08:35,824
Oh, that kid who was here left,
saying that you guys would pay.

141
00:08:37,104 --> 00:08:39,538
That guy!
How dare he make fools of us!

142
00:08:40,808 --> 00:08:43,743
<i>The sound of footsteps is far off...</i>
<i>He has considerable speed!</i>

143
00:08:44,612 --> 00:08:46,546
He made us look like idiots!

144
00:08:46,614 --> 00:08:49,082
I can't stay quiet.
We have to chase him!

145
00:08:51,118 --> 00:08:54,451
Missus, thank you very much.
I'll leave the money here.

146
00:08:55,322 --> 00:08:56,016
Thanks!

147
00:08:57,224 --> 00:08:59,818
All the customers today
seem to be in such a hurry.

148
00:09:01,929 --> 00:09:04,955
He has incredible speed.
He must have trained very hard.

149
00:09:05,566 --> 00:09:06,590
Who is he?

150
00:09:06,801 --> 00:09:09,634
Doesn't matter, we're definitely
going to catch up to him!

151
00:09:12,873 --> 00:09:14,568
Stupid Ninja!

152
00:09:15,076 --> 00:09:16,475
There's no way
they can catch up to me!

153
00:09:30,357 --> 00:09:31,381
Owww!

154
00:09:32,293 --> 00:09:35,888
Darn it... Swift Runner Idate
makes a mistake of a lifetime!

155
00:09:39,967 --> 00:09:41,264
Serves you right!

156
00:09:45,439 --> 00:09:48,704
You have some nerve,
trying to run away from us.

157
00:09:50,678 --> 00:09:51,770
I'm so sorry!

158
00:09:52,646 --> 00:09:53,237
Huh?

159
00:09:53,647 --> 00:09:54,773
I'm sorry...

160
00:09:55,182 --> 00:09:59,812
I had my wallet stolen and was at a loss,
then you guys showed up.

161
00:10:00,020 --> 00:10:01,612
So I did that...

162
00:10:04,191 --> 00:10:06,284
You kinda feel sorry
after hearing his story.

163
00:10:06,560 --> 00:10:09,552
Then you should have said that
from the start!

164
00:10:09,697 --> 00:10:10,595
Ow! Huh...?

165
00:10:12,800 --> 00:10:13,960
What's this?

166
00:10:14,201 --> 00:10:14,929
Don't touch it!

167
00:10:18,305 --> 00:10:19,397
This is mine!

168
00:10:21,509 --> 00:10:22,601
Wh-What the...?!

169
00:10:24,378 --> 00:10:25,538
On your mark.

170
00:10:26,947 --> 00:10:27,936
Get set...

171
00:10:28,616 --> 00:10:29,378
Go!

172
00:10:30,351 --> 00:10:31,010
Weights?

173
00:10:32,153 --> 00:10:34,815
Try to catch me now, you idiots!

174
00:10:35,556 --> 00:10:37,217
Hey! He escaped again!

175
00:10:37,324 --> 00:10:38,518
That guy!

176
00:10:39,927 --> 00:10:40,951
He simply doesn't get it!

177
00:10:45,499 --> 00:10:46,329
Is he for real?

178
00:10:46,734 --> 00:10:48,031
What a speed...!

179
00:10:50,838 --> 00:10:53,466
No way!
Even we can't catch up to him?

180
00:10:57,978 --> 00:11:00,742
That's it. We don't have a chance
of catching up.

181
00:11:01,015 --> 00:11:05,213
Dang it! He'll get it
when I see him next time!

182
00:11:11,693 --> 00:11:14,025
All of you, thanks for coming.

183
00:11:15,229 --> 00:11:17,823
Begging your pardon!
Begging your pardon!

184
00:11:18,132 --> 00:11:22,501
I was born and raised
in the Leaf Village in the Land of Fire.

185
00:11:22,603 --> 00:11:25,071
I was bathed in birth water
at "Ichiraku Ramen."

186
00:11:25,173 --> 00:11:27,403
My given name is Naruto
and the surname is Uzumaki.

187
00:11:27,475 --> 00:11:28,840
People call me...

188
00:11:28,910 --> 00:11:30,002
Loser!

189
00:11:30,211 --> 00:11:33,339
Loser? Nah, not that!

190
00:11:35,249 --> 00:11:36,841
You're funny as usual.

191
00:11:38,086 --> 00:11:40,384
Boss Jirocho,
you're looking good yourself.

192
00:11:40,555 --> 00:11:41,681
Hey, Naruto!

193
00:11:43,124 --> 00:11:46,958
That's okay.
A boy should be this spunky.

194
00:11:47,929 --> 00:11:50,727
The greetings seem to be done,
so I'll get to the main topic.

195
00:11:51,532 --> 00:11:54,729
The Fifth Hokage told us to get
the details of this mission from you.

196
00:11:56,104 --> 00:11:58,004
Yes, in fact...

197
00:12:00,875 --> 00:12:05,642
Do you know of the Dedication Ceremony
at the Todoroki Great Shrine?

198
00:12:06,380 --> 00:12:08,507
To... Todo... what?

199
00:12:09,183 --> 00:12:10,912
Well, make yourselves comfortable.

200
00:12:13,788 --> 00:12:15,346
The legend goes...

201
00:12:18,960 --> 00:12:21,793
A long time ago,
in order to subdue a storm,

202
00:12:21,996 --> 00:12:25,432
Ryuko's Jewels were dedicated
to the Todoroki Great Shrine

203
00:12:25,700 --> 00:12:28,828
and the storm subsided.

204
00:12:30,404 --> 00:12:33,271
It became a customary event
that happens once every four years.

205
00:12:34,742 --> 00:12:38,974
At first, it was just to dedicate the jewels,
but several decades ago,

206
00:12:39,046 --> 00:12:40,513
it became a festival in which
the first-place runner

207
00:12:40,581 --> 00:12:42,481
became the man of the year.

208
00:12:45,186 --> 00:12:49,850
In recent years, the festival has
taken on another face.

209
00:12:51,626 --> 00:12:54,220
For ages now,
in this port town of Degarashi,

210
00:12:54,295 --> 00:12:57,423
two families,
the Wasabi and the Wagarashi,

211
00:12:57,498 --> 00:13:00,023
have controlled local operations
and policed the town.

212
00:13:01,435 --> 00:13:02,868
It's embarrassing,

213
00:13:03,070 --> 00:13:05,402
but conflict between the two families
has never ceased and

214
00:13:05,773 --> 00:13:09,106
there have been numerous skirmishes
over territorial rights.

215
00:13:10,478 --> 00:13:12,343
As the struggle intensified,

216
00:13:12,547 --> 00:13:16,415
the town residents became entangled
and even got injured...

217
00:13:18,920 --> 00:13:21,684
In order to put a stop to the conflict,
for the first time,

218
00:13:21,989 --> 00:13:26,016
there was talk of some kind of mediation
in the presence of the lord.

219
00:13:27,862 --> 00:13:30,558
And it was agreed that the power holder
of the town

220
00:13:30,631 --> 00:13:33,099
would be determined in a contest
rather than through brawls.

221
00:13:34,602 --> 00:13:36,365
So that contest is...

222
00:13:37,071 --> 00:13:38,834
It is the Todoroki Great Shrine
Dedication Ceremony

223
00:13:38,906 --> 00:13:41,704
that is held every four years.

224
00:13:44,011 --> 00:13:47,777
Four years ago, the Wagarashi
easily won by hiring a Shinobi,

225
00:13:47,882 --> 00:13:51,215
and we have learned that
they've hired a Shinobi again this year.

226
00:13:52,153 --> 00:13:53,381
In order to counteract that,

227
00:13:53,454 --> 00:13:57,982
we sent messengers to
the Hidden Leaf Village with a request,

228
00:13:58,960 --> 00:14:01,793
but they were ambushed and attacked.

229
00:14:10,872 --> 00:14:11,702
I beg you guys!

230
00:14:13,140 --> 00:14:14,767
Please lend us your power.

231
00:14:15,443 --> 00:14:19,641
We cannot afford to lose this race
to the Wagarashi Family!

232
00:14:21,749 --> 00:14:23,717
Leave it to me!

233
00:14:24,051 --> 00:14:26,212
And, who do you want us
to escort?

234
00:14:26,921 --> 00:14:29,082
Oh, so you'll take this job?

235
00:14:33,060 --> 00:14:34,493
Did you call for me, Boss?

236
00:14:43,371 --> 00:14:46,738
Oh, you guys know each other?
Then that makes the story fast.

237
00:14:49,543 --> 00:14:50,805
That might not actually
be the case...

238
00:14:55,316 --> 00:14:57,614
Boss Jirocho is an important person!

239
00:14:58,119 --> 00:15:01,350
By rights, he shouldn't bow
his head to Ninja like you!

240
00:15:02,323 --> 00:15:07,420
Even if he did bow his head,
I'd flatly refuse to escort a guy like you.

241
00:15:07,662 --> 00:15:08,356
Oh yeah?!

242
00:15:08,529 --> 00:15:13,626
As if I'd go with some guy who came
from who knows where!

243
00:15:14,068 --> 00:15:15,899
"Some guy from who knows where"?!

244
00:15:16,237 --> 00:15:18,831
I am the brilliant Ninja,
Naruto Uzumaki,

245
00:15:18,906 --> 00:15:21,136
who will eventually inherit
the name of Hokage!

246
00:15:21,375 --> 00:15:23,605
Hah! Hokage is no big deal!

247
00:15:23,711 --> 00:15:26,509
Hah! The boss of hooligans
is even less of a big deal!

248
00:15:26,814 --> 00:15:29,874
You idiot! Boss Jirocho is
a very honorable person!

249
00:15:30,117 --> 00:15:32,085
The Hokage is a great Shinobi

250
00:15:32,153 --> 00:15:35,316
who puts his life on the line
to protect the village!

251
00:15:35,523 --> 00:15:38,686
Boss Jirocho is a very,
very, very honorable person

252
00:15:38,759 --> 00:15:41,660
who always puts his life
on the line to protect the town!

253
00:15:41,896 --> 00:15:45,992
Hokage is more, more,
more incredible!

254
00:15:59,313 --> 00:16:02,771
<i>Even though it's a tourist resort,</i>
<i>everything seems so expensive.</i>

255
00:16:03,084 --> 00:16:05,484
Sorry about that.
It sure is expensive, isn't it?

256
00:16:05,686 --> 00:16:06,846
Oh no, I didn't mean...

257
00:16:07,388 --> 00:16:09,982
We actually don't want to sell
at this kind of price,

258
00:16:10,057 --> 00:16:12,389
but after the Wagarashi family
came into power...

259
00:16:13,995 --> 00:16:15,485
P-Please forgive me!

260
00:16:15,563 --> 00:16:16,461
How dare you?!

261
00:16:16,530 --> 00:16:19,158
Do you know who you have
to thank to do business?

262
00:16:19,266 --> 00:16:21,928
Are you actually thinking about turning
against the Wagarashi Family?

263
00:16:22,269 --> 00:16:26,069
N-Not at all.
But I have to get paid...

264
00:16:26,240 --> 00:16:28,708
You're slow to understand.

265
00:16:29,043 --> 00:16:30,010
- Hey!
- Yes, sir!

266
00:16:30,911 --> 00:16:32,469
P-Please stop!

267
00:16:33,581 --> 00:16:36,209
Huh! First of all, we'll destroy you...

268
00:16:38,019 --> 00:16:39,543
Wh-Who are you?!

269
00:16:40,888 --> 00:16:43,015
Get out of here before you get hurt!

270
00:16:43,524 --> 00:16:44,388
- What?!
- What?!

271
00:16:44,759 --> 00:16:45,885
Please run away!

272
00:16:46,027 --> 00:16:47,654
These people are from
the Wagarashi...

273
00:16:47,728 --> 00:16:48,695
It'll be fine.

274
00:16:49,397 --> 00:16:50,591
- You punk!
- Wise guy!

275
00:16:56,670 --> 00:16:58,831
We'll let you go for today!

276
00:16:59,040 --> 00:17:01,907
If you've learned your lesson,
never defy us again, kid!

277
00:17:03,878 --> 00:17:05,869
Or you'll pay when
we see you next time!

278
00:17:10,384 --> 00:17:12,352
- Y-You won't get away with this!
- Y-You won't get away with this!

279
00:17:13,421 --> 00:17:14,251
Young man...

280
00:17:15,890 --> 00:17:17,289
Thank you very much.

281
00:17:17,925 --> 00:17:19,790
What a refreshing feeling!

282
00:17:20,127 --> 00:17:23,995
We <i>definitely</i> need Boss Jirocho's
Wasabi Family to win the upcoming race.

283
00:17:25,766 --> 00:17:26,596
Sasuke...

284
00:17:27,301 --> 00:17:27,926
Yeah...

285
00:17:40,414 --> 00:17:41,108
Boss...

286
00:17:41,715 --> 00:17:44,206
Of all people,
did you have to ask the Leaf Shinobi?

287
00:17:46,654 --> 00:17:48,315
Don't sulk like that, Idate.

288
00:17:49,223 --> 00:17:50,247
I'm not sulking.

289
00:17:51,292 --> 00:17:52,088
It's just that...

290
00:17:53,294 --> 00:17:54,124
Idate...

291
00:17:55,029 --> 00:17:57,520
I believe in you more
than anybody else.

292
00:17:58,699 --> 00:18:00,098
The rest depends on you.

293
00:18:01,402 --> 00:18:03,962
Why don't you believe
in people a little?

294
00:18:13,013 --> 00:18:13,945
Idate...

295
00:18:14,715 --> 00:18:16,706
please run for this town.

296
00:18:17,852 --> 00:18:18,546
I beg you!

297
00:18:19,720 --> 00:18:20,448
Boss...

298
00:18:22,223 --> 00:18:22,985
Okay.

299
00:18:24,024 --> 00:18:25,651
<i>Even in exchange for my life...</i>

300
00:18:36,971 --> 00:18:40,873
Wow, I didn't think it was going
to be this big

301
00:18:41,175 --> 00:18:42,870
But what kind of race is it?

302
00:18:43,410 --> 00:18:47,346
I'll explain the course so
a dummy like you can understand.

303
00:18:48,182 --> 00:18:50,548
The starting point is Degarashi Port.

304
00:18:51,085 --> 00:18:54,350
After the start, you head for
Modoroki Shrine which is the midway point.

305
00:18:54,588 --> 00:18:56,488
This is Modoroki Shrine...?

306
00:18:56,790 --> 00:18:59,452
Yes... It seems the fastest way
to get to Modoroki Shrine

307
00:18:59,527 --> 00:19:01,688
is to use a boat from here.

308
00:19:02,396 --> 00:19:05,854
Then you take one of two Ryuko's jewels
from Modoroki Shrine and

309
00:19:05,933 --> 00:19:09,425
dedicate that jewel at the
Todoroki Great Shrine on Ouzu Island.

310
00:19:10,371 --> 00:19:12,771
That's the only rule
for the race.

311
00:19:13,107 --> 00:19:17,271
So shortcuts, obstructions,
and secret maneuvers are all allowed.

312
00:19:18,479 --> 00:19:21,312
So hiring a Ninja is not
a violation of the rule either.

313
00:19:21,882 --> 00:19:24,680
Who are the Ninja that
the other side hired?

314
00:19:25,186 --> 00:19:27,552
They're hiding somewhere
and checking the situation.

315
00:19:28,122 --> 00:19:29,851
Don't be careless, Naruto!

316
00:19:29,957 --> 00:19:31,254
R-Right!

317
00:19:31,625 --> 00:19:35,493
You guys can just relax and watch.
Don't follow me around!

318
00:19:35,563 --> 00:19:36,587
What?!

319
00:19:36,730 --> 00:19:38,994
I'm saying I don't want
an impediment.

320
00:19:39,300 --> 00:19:40,164
You!

321
00:19:40,234 --> 00:19:42,464
Calm down.
Let's join forces here.

322
00:19:42,536 --> 00:19:44,697
- Not with a guy like this!
- Not with a guy like this!

323
00:19:45,472 --> 00:19:48,600
<i>They seem to strangely be</i>
<i>in harmony, these two.</i>

324
00:19:49,610 --> 00:19:50,941
<i>All right, everybody!</i>

325
00:19:51,011 --> 00:19:54,378
<i>The Todoroki Great Shrine Race</i>
<i>will start soon!</i>

326
00:19:54,715 --> 00:19:57,411
<i>Wasabi Family's runner,</i>
<i>Idate Morino!</i>

327
00:20:02,990 --> 00:20:04,855
<i>Idate...Morino?</i>

328
00:20:05,659 --> 00:20:09,322
<i>Wagarashi Family's runner,</i>
<i>Fukusuke Hikyakuya!</i>

329
00:20:16,270 --> 00:20:17,601
<i>On your mark!</i>

330
00:20:40,995 --> 00:20:42,257
<i>Start!</i>

331
00:20:43,897 --> 00:20:46,331
All right! We're going too!

332
00:20:46,567 --> 00:20:47,727
Wh-What the?!

333
00:20:50,437 --> 00:20:51,267
Is he running away?!

334
00:20:51,405 --> 00:20:53,202
Where are you going, Idate?!

335
00:20:53,440 --> 00:20:55,601
Hey, wait!

336
00:20:56,243 --> 00:20:57,835
<i>Wh-What is he doing...?</i>

337
00:21:01,782 --> 00:21:04,012
Wait!

338
00:21:07,354 --> 00:21:12,053
<i>I believe your promise,</i>
<i>its a true heart give me courage</i>

339
00:21:12,126 --> 00:21:16,460
<i>Always I feel it</i>
<i>the precious time with you</i>

340
00:21:17,064 --> 00:21:20,591
<i>On your still shoulder</i>

341
00:21:21,835 --> 00:21:26,295
<i>I feel the wind that blows</i>
<i>towards tomorrow</i>

342
00:21:26,473 --> 00:21:31,911
<i>The city lights are like pieces of stars</i>

343
00:21:32,413 --> 00:21:36,713
<i>That hold us together</i>

344
00:21:37,184 --> 00:21:46,422
<i>"Each one of us glows differently,"</i>

345
00:21:46,493 --> 00:21:49,087
<i>you say laughingly</i>

346
00:21:49,330 --> 00:21:54,996
<i>but you look most dazzling</i>

347
00:21:55,569 --> 00:21:59,938
<i>Like a comet,</i>

348
00:22:00,007 --> 00:22:06,105
<i>like the rainbow after the storm</i>

349
00:22:06,180 --> 00:22:13,279
<i>You bring light into my heart</i>

350
00:22:14,288 --> 00:22:23,663
<i>Being lost can be the answer</i>

351
00:22:24,998 --> 00:22:32,530
<i>Let's promise we won't cheat</i>

352
00:22:32,606 --> 00:22:36,599
<i>Uh...like a shooting star,</i>
<i>we do go ahead.</i>

353
00:22:39,346 --> 00:22:41,780
What the heck is he thinking?!
That idiot!

354
00:22:41,949 --> 00:22:45,112
So fast. He's moving at
an incredible speed.

355
00:22:45,185 --> 00:22:47,949
Darn it! The opponent's already
far out at sea!

356
00:22:48,021 --> 00:22:48,646
This is bad!

357
00:22:48,789 --> 00:22:51,223
If the distance between them gets
any greater, it'll be impossible to win!

358
00:22:51,291 --> 00:22:52,189
That idiot!

359
00:22:52,292 --> 00:22:54,283
- Kick it up a notch, Sakura!
- Right!

360
00:22:54,361 --> 00:22:57,990
We're gonna bring him back at all cost
and make up the difference!

361
00:22:58,932 --> 00:23:02,993
Next time: "The Race is On!
Trouble on the High Seas!"

362
00:23:03,337 --> 00:23:04,861
Don't miss it!
